class DependencyTracker: Track dependencies during execution
TEST = '<test>'
__enter__(self) -> Any: Track entering an if/while/for block
__exit__(self, exc_type: Type, exc_value: BaseException, traceback: traceback) -> Optional[bool]: Track exiting an if/while/for block
__init__(self, *args: Any, **kwargs: Any) -> None: Constructor. Arguments are passed to DataTracker.__init__()
arg(self, value: Any, pos: Optional[int] = None, kw: Optional[str] = None) -> Any: Track passing an argument `value` (with given position `pos` 1..n or keyword `kw`)
call(self, func: Callable) -> Callable: Track a call of function `func`
get(self, name: str, value: Any) -> Any: Track a read access for variable `name` with value `value`

param(self, name: str, value: Any, pos: Optional[int] = None, vararg: str = '', last: bool = False) -> Any: Track getting a parameter `name` with value `value` (with given position `pos`). vararg parameters are indicated by setting `varargs` to '*' (*args) or '**' (**kwargs)
ret(self, value: Any) -> Any: Track a function return
set(self, name: str, value: Any, loads: Optional[Set[str]] = None) -> Any: Add a dependency for `name` = `value`
test(self, value: Any) -> Any: Track a test for condition `value`
call_generator(self, func: Callable) -> Callable: Track a call of a generator function
check_location(self) -> None: If we are in a new location, clear set of read variables
clear_read(self) -> None: Clear set of read variables
dependencies(self) -> Dependencies: Return dependencies
ignore_location_change(self) -> None
ignore_next_location_change(self) -> None
in_generator(self) -> bool: True if we are calling a generator function
ret_generator(self, generator: Any) -> Any: Track the return of a generator function
class DataTracker: Track data accesses during execution
__enter__(self) -> Any: Enter `with` block. To be overloaded in subclasses.
__exit__(self, exc_type: Type, exc_value: BaseException, traceback: traceback) -> Optional[bool]: Exit `with` block. To be overloaded in subclasses.
__init__(self, log: bool = False) -> None: Constructor. If `log` is set, turn on logging.

arg(self, value: Any, pos: Optional[int] = None, kw: Optional[str] = None) -> Any: Track `value` being passed as argument. `pos` (if given) is the argument position (starting with 1). `kw` (if given) is the argument keyword.
augment(self, name: str, value: Any) -> Any: Track augmenting `name` with `value`. To be overloaded in subclasses.
call(self, func: Callable) -> Callable: Track a call to `func`.
get(self, name: str, value: Any) -> Any: Track getting `value` from `name`.

param(self, name: str, value: Any, pos: Optional[int] = None, vararg: str = '', last: bool = False) -> Any: At the beginning of a function, track parameter `name` being set to `value`. `pos` is the position of the argument (starting with 1). `vararg` is "*" if `name` is a vararg parameter (as in *args), and "**" is `name` is a kwargs parameter (as in *kwargs). `last` is True if `name` is the last parameter.
ret(self, value: Any) -> Any: Track `value` being used as return value.
set(self, name: str, value: Any, loads: Optional[Set[str]] = None) -> Any: Track setting `name` to `value`.
test(self, cond: ast.AST) -> ast.AST: Test condition `cond`. To be overloaded in subclasses.
instrument_call(self, func: Callable) -> Callable: Instrument a call to `func`. To be implemented in subclasses.
class Dependencies: A dependency graph
FONT_NAME = 'Courier'
NODE_COLOR = 'peachpuff'

__init__(self, data: Optional[Dict[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]], Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]]] = None, control: Optional[Dict[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]], Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]]] = None) -> None: Create a dependency graph from `data` and `control`. Both `data` and `control` are dictionaries holding _nodes_ as keys and sets of nodes as values. Each node comes as a tuple (variable_name, location) where `variable_name` is a string and `location` is a pair (function, lineno) where `function` is a callable and `lineno` is a line number denoting a unique location in the code.
__repr__(self) -> str: Represent dependencies as a Python expression
__str__(self) -> str: Return string representation of dependencies
_repr_mimebundle_(self, include: Any = None, exclude: Any = None) -> Any: If the object is output in Jupyter, render dependencies as a SVG graph

all_functions(self) -> Dict[Callable, List[Tuple[int, Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]]]: Return mapping {`function`: [(`lineno`, `var`), (`lineno`, `var`), ...], ...} for all functions in the dependencies.
all_vars(self) -> Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]: Return a set of all variables (as `var_name`, `location`) in the dependencies

backward_slice(self, *criteria: Union[str, Tuple[Callable, int], Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]], mode: str = 'cd', depth: int = -1) -> Dependencies: Create a backward slice from nodes `criteria`. `mode` can contain 'c' (draw control dependencies) and 'd' (draw data dependencies) (default: 'cd')

code(self, *items: Callable, mode: str = 'cd') -> None: List `items` on standard output, including dependencies as comments. If `items` is empty, all included functions are listed. `mode` can contain 'c' (draw control dependencies) and 'd' (draw data dependencies) (default: 'cd').

graph(self, *, mode: str = 'flow') -> graphviz.graphs.Digraph: Draw dependencies. `mode` is either * `'flow'`: arrows indicate information flow (from A to B); or * `'depend'`: arrows indicate dependencies (B depends on A)
_code(self, item: Callable, mode: str) -> None
_source(self, node: Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str
add_hierarchy(self, g: graphviz.graphs.Digraph) -> graphviz.graphs.Digraph: Add invisible edges for a proper hierarchy.
draw_dependencies(self, g: graphviz.graphs.Digraph, mode: str) -> None
draw_edge(self, g: graphviz.graphs.Digraph, mode: str, node_from: str, node_to: str, **kwargs: Any) -> None
expand_criteria(self, criteria: List[Union[str, Tuple[Callable, int], Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]]) -> List[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]: Return list of vars matched by `criteria`.
format_var(self, var: Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]], current_func: Optional[Callable] = None) -> str: Return string for `var` in `current_func`.
id(self, var: Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str: Return a unique ID for `var`.
label(self, var: Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str: Render node `var` using HTML style.
make_graph(self, name: str = 'dependencies', comment: str = 'Dependencies') -> graphviz.graphs.Digraph
repr_dependencies(self, vars: Dict[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]], Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]]) -> str
repr_deps(self, var_set: Set[Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]]) -> str
repr_var(self, var: Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str
source(self, node: Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str: Return the source code for a given node.
tooltip(self, var: Tuple[str, Tuple[Callable, int]]) -> str: Return a tooltip for node `var`.
validate(self) -> None: Perform a simple syntactic validation of dependencies
